Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Software Engineer II position with Horace Mann. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack software development, cloud-native systems, and collaborative engineering, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade software applications that directly reflect the technical depth and collaborative approach this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I participated in the full development lifecycle of an MCP AI interaction layer, completing design, development, testing, and debugging activities to translate natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints — requiring rigorous API contract design, input validation, and ensuring application performance, reliability, and quality standards are met. To maintain system stability, I diagnosed and resolved system issues, bugs, and performance challenges by implementing an observability layer using Langfuse and LangSmith for tracing and structured logs, reducing latency by 60% and LLM API costs by 50%. I also developed, enhanced, and maintained generative code solutions including API-aware templates and SDK patterns to accelerate platform API integration, including upgrades and patches to existing systems. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to infrastructure that thousands of users rely on daily. I developed and maintained a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that handles file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO — giving me hands-on experience with multi-environment backend design and web technologies. I also contributed to the design, development, and maintenance of an Identity & Access Management platform built with React, Spring Boot, Java, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications with a focus on quality standards. Additionally, I developed backend workflows using AWS Step Functions and scripting tools to handle long-running data import jobs, collaborating with DevOps teams to support system stability and CI/CD processes while maintaining technical documentation. Together, these roles have prepared me to contribute meaningfully to software development and maintenance activities while working collaboratively with cross-functional teams.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in technical problem-solving and mentorship — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and collaborative culture this team values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion to generate fashion designs using CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA on Pace University's HPC cluster, following SDLC methodologies and best practices throughout the development process. Beyond building the systems myself, I provided feedback and guidance to less experienced engineers (50+ students) through workshops on GPU programming and building AI Agents, demonstrating effective communication with technical and non-technical stakeholders. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring the mentorship and knowledge-sharing responsibilities central to this role. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to Horace Mann's engineering team.

I have always been passionate about serving educators and supporting the educational community, and I deeply respect Horace Mann's commitment to the lifelong financial well-being of educators and their families. I envision myself contributing my technical talent to furthering Horace Mann's mission of delivering reliable and scalable technology solutions that serve educators. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

